      "writtenOn": "2020-05-08T14:53:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "After some more thought, I yet think it is better to drop this.\n1. I doubt that \"^x.*\" is main usage scenario.\n2. If we want to filter files with some extention, we need to write \u0027.*\\.pyc\u0027 instead of \u0027\\.pyc$\u0027 which is bit longer and appearence is not so explicit.\n3. Also we want to exclude \u0027.git\u0027 directory by default, and \u0027/\\.git/\u0027 is shorter than \u0027.*/\\.git/.*\u0027.\nhttps://cs.chromium.org/chromium/infra/go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/client/isolate/isolate.go?l\u003d93\u0026rcl\u003d4d2a6af1f9bbd97375d92a5985311a7cc50b6f06",
